SUMMARY:Operation Mincemeat: A New Musical
LOCATION:Golden Theatre, 252 West 45th Street, New York NY 10036
DESCRIPTION:<p><em>Operation Mincemeat</em> is the 2024 Olivier
  Award-winning Best New Musical , the 2025 Tony Award&reg; winner for Best
  Featured Actor in a Musical (Jak Malone), and was named the #1 Broadway
  Show of 2025 (<em>Entertainment Weekly</em>).<br /><br />The year is 1943
  and right now we&rsquo;re losing the war. Luckily, we&rsquo;re about to
  gamble all our futures on a stolen corpse. Bursting at the seams with the
  kind of chaos you couldn&rsquo;t invent, the question is: how did a dead
  body, a fake love letter, and-of all people-Ian Fleming come together to
  wrong-foot Hitler?<br /><br />&ldquo;It's not just the best musical
  I&rsquo;ve ever seen; it&rsquo;s the most rewarding theatrical experience
  I&rsquo;ve ever had.&rdquo; - Taffy Brodesser-Akner, <em>The New York
  Times Magazine</em><br /><br />&ldquo;The reviews have been ecstatic. The
  overwhelming impression is of hopefulness, possibility, and joy.&rdquo;
  &mdash; <em>The New York Times</em><br /><br />&ldquo;The Brits have made
  the year&rsquo;s funniest musical.&rdquo; &mdash; Peter Marks, <em>The
  Washington Post</em><br /><br />&ldquo;The best new song on
  Broadway&hellip; that song will be sung for the next hundred years.&rdquo;
  &mdash; <em>Vulture</em><br /><br />&ldquo;Part Mel Brooks, part
  <em>SIX</em>, part <em>Hamilton</em> with a side order of <em>One Man, Two
  Guvnors</em>.&rdquo; &mdash; <em>The Daily Mirror</em><br /><br
  />&ldquo;Too British? Not if you want to laugh uproariously &mdash; and
  perhaps even unexpectedly shed a tear or two.&rdquo; &mdash;
  <em>Variety<br /><br /></em>&ldquo;A laugh-out-loud delight, with endless
  charm&hellip; There&rsquo;s nothing else like it on Broadway.&rdquo;  -
  <em>Entertainment Weekly</em></p>
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR